Package gov.sandia.geotess.extensions.earthinterface

Enum EarthInterface

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Enum<EarthInterface>
gov.sandia.geotess.extensions.earthinterface.EarthInterface
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Comparable<EarthInterface>, java.lang.constant.Constable
public enum EarthInterface extends Enum<EarthInterface>
A specification of ordered Earth Interfaces used by the GeoTessModelEarthInterface extension of the GeoTessModel. This fixes the nameing convention and order of Earth interface layer names which is necessary for applications that must determine layers given other types of information such as seismic phase definitions (e.g. The Bender Phase object).
Author:
jrhipp

    • repair

      public static String repair(String name)
      Static method that can be called in method GeoTessMetaData.setEarthInterfaceLayers(String ...) to replace old model type names with their corresponding new EarthInterface name.
      Parameters:
      name - The name to be replaced (if not a valid name).
      Returns:
      The input name if it is already defined in EarthInterface, or the Correct name if the input name matches one of the names checked for in the repair map, or the original name if the name is an error and a match cannot be found. In the last case the method setEarthInterfaceLayers will throw an error indicating that the name is invalid.
